      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "In cmpv2_provisioner CSR and private Key is taken from signCertificateModel, so why here there are passed as separate params?\n\nI have checked and CSR is filtered one, but private Key not.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2021-07-16 07:59:24.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "0e60bbfa_40bbd39b",
      "file_path": "certServiceK8sExternalProvider/src/certserviceclient/cert_service_client.go",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "CSR is filtered -it mean that we removed unsupported parameters in CertServiceAPI; postal code, street addres, serial number. Private key not required filtering. \n\nIt is passed ass separate parameter to keep similar declaration in client. \nGetCertificates(csr []byte, key []byte)\nUpdateCertificate(csr []byte, key []byte, signCertificateModel model.SignCertificateModel) \n\nIt could be refactored in separate commit.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6310,
        "name": "Tomasz Wr�bel",
        "display_name": "Tomasz Wrobel",
        "email": "tomasz.wrobel@nokia.com",
